Paper: hep-th/9404123

Date: 1994-04-20

Title: Time Measurement in Quantum Gravity

Authors: N.Itzhaki

Comments: 4 pages, TAUP-2087-93

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B328 (1994) 274-276

We discuss time measurement in quantum gravity. Using general relativity forlarge distances and the uncertainty principle we find a minimum time intervalof the order of the Planck time, therefore the uncertainty in time measurmentis bounded from below.